Enum Merge.FlagT

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<Merge.FlagT>
      • com.github.git24j.core.Merge.FlagT

    Merge

    public static enum Merge.FlagT
extends Enum<Merge.FlagT>
implements IBitEnum
    Flags for `git_merge` options. A combination of these flags can be passed in via the `flags` value in the `git_merge_options`.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      FAIL_ON_CONFLICT
      If a conflict occurs, exit immediately instead of attempting to continue resolving conflicts.
      FIND_RENAMES
      Detect renames that occur between the common ancestor and the "ours" side or the common ancestor and the "theirs" side.
      NO_RECURSIVE
      If the commits being merged have multiple merge bases, do not build a recursive merge base (by merging the multiple merge bases), instead simply use the first base.
      SKIP_REUC
      Do not write the REUC extension on the generated index

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • FIND_RENAMES

        public static final Merge.FlagT FIND_RENAMES
        Detect renames that occur between the common ancestor and the "ours" side or the common ancestor and the "theirs" side. This will enable the ability to merge between a modified and renamed file.

      • FAIL_ON_CONFLICT

        public static final Merge.FlagT FAIL_ON_CONFLICT
        If a conflict occurs, exit immediately instead of attempting to continue resolving conflicts. The merge operation will fail with GIT_EMERGECONFLICT and no index will be returned.

      • SKIP_REUC

        public static final Merge.FlagT SKIP_REUC
        Do not write the REUC extension on the generated index

      • NO_RECURSIVE

        public static final Merge.FlagT NO_RECURSIVE
        If the commits being merged have multiple merge bases, do not build a recursive merge base (by merging the multiple merge bases), instead simply use the first base. This flag provides a similar merge base to `git-merge-resolve`.
